;(Talk to Qingque)
:{{A|VO side2 baishi mar7th 296.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' I'm going up against Skott soon. Do you know why I'm visiting you, Qingque?
:{{A|VO side2 baishi qingque 101 m.ogg}} {{A|VO side2 baishi qingque 101 f.ogg}} '''Qingque:''' Yeah, with you, me, and (Trailblazer) here, the answer is pretty obvious.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} We can brainstorm ways to defeat Skott together.
::{{A|VO side2 baishi qingque 102.ogg}} '''Qingque:''' But I know nothing about swordplay or duels. Now, if you're talking about playing Celestial Jade, that's something I might be able to help with.
::Of course, we're here to play "Celestial Jade!"
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Of course, we're here to play "Celestial Jade!"
:{{A|VO side2 baishi qingque 103.ogg}} '''Qingque:''' Yeah, you just have pre-fight jitters, March. Let's play a couple of rounds to help you relax.
:{{A|VO side2 baishi mar7th 297.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' Wait a minute! I've been playing with you a lot lately, right? I've actually picked up a few insights. For example, I've been thinking lately that just defeating Skott with my swords might not be enough...
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} You? Thinking?
::{{A|VO side2 baishi mar7th 298.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' ...Yeah. You don't really think I'm dumb, do you?
::Care to share your insights?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Care to share your insights?
:{{A|VO side2 baishi mar7th 299.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' Well, here's the thing. Even if Skott apologizes, do you think he'd actually feel sorry for what he did?
:{{A|VO side2 baishi qingque 104.ogg}} '''Qingque:''' Nah, it's more he's just honoring a bet. Whether it's apologizing or squealing like a pig, I doubt he'd do it willingly.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Remember when he barked like a dog? He definitely wasn't sorry then.
::{{A|VO side2 baishi mar7th 300.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' Exactly! He just wants to show off, which is why he picked Aurum Alley as the venue.
::But defeating him like this would feel pretty satisfying!
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} But defeating him like this would feel pretty satisfying!
:{{A|VO side2 baishi mar7th 301.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' True heroes in Immersia don't merely settle for "satisfying!"
:{{A|VO side2 baishi qingque 105.ogg}} '''Qingque:''' ...You're right. Even though I'm not a fan, I'll help you figure something out.
:{{A|VO side2 baishi mar7th 302 m.ogg}} {{A|VO side2 baishi mar7th 302 f.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' (Trailblazer), why don't you fill her in on what happened at Aurum Alley earlier?
:Qingque listens to the whole story of Skott's incident with great interest.
:By the time you finish speaking, you notice that there seems to be a hint of anger on Qingque's face.
:{{A|VO side2 baishi qingque 106.ogg}} '''Qingque:''' If being a workaholic were a disease, Skott would be in the ICU! It's okay to enjoy your work, but causing trouble in society is another story!
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} So, any suggestions on what to do?
::{{A|VO side2 baishi qingque 107.ogg}} '''Qingque:''' I don't have suggestions, only an opinion, and that is "He's a hopeless workaholic."
::He deserves a good scolding!
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} He deserves a good scolding!
:{{A|VO side2 baishi qingque 108.ogg}} '''Qingque:''' Skott really needs to apologize to regular people like me.
:{{A|VO side2 baishi qingque 109.ogg}} '''Qingque:''' Come on, March! Let's go find him!
:{{tx}}

{{Dialogue End}}

